1081-<div class="sectionbody">
1082-<div class="paragraph">
1083:<p>Spring Boot jars include metadata files that provide details of all supported configuration properties.
1084:The files are designed to let IDE developers offer contextual help and &#8220;code completion&#8221; as users are working with <code>application.properties</code> or <code>application.yaml</code> files.</p>
1085-</div>
1086-<div class="paragraph">
1087:<p>The majority of the metadata file is generated automatically at compile time by processing all items annotated with <code>@ConfigurationProperties</code>.
1088-However, it is possible to <a href="#appendix.configuration-metadata.annotation-processor.adding-additional-metadata">write part of the metadata manually</a> for corner cases or more advanced use cases.</p>
1089-</div>
--
1094-<div class="sectionbody">
1095-<div class="paragraph">
1096:<p>Configuration metadata files are located inside jars under <code>META-INF/spring-configuration-metadata.json</code>.
1097-They use a JSON format with items categorized under either &#8220;groups&#8221; or &#8220;properties&#8221; and additional values hints categorized under "hints", as shown in the following example:</p>
1098-</div>
--
1197-<div class="paragraph">
1198-<p>Finally, &#8220;hints&#8221; are additional information used to assist the user in configuring a given property.
1199:For example, when a developer is configuring the <code>spring.jpa.hibernate.ddl-auto</code> property, a tool can use the hints to offer some auto-completion help for the <code>none</code>, <code>validate</code>, <code>update</code>, <code>create</code>, and <code>create-drop</code> values.</p>
1200-</div>
1201-<div class="sect2">
--
1542-<h3 id="appendix.configuration-metadata.format.repeated-items"><a class="anchor" href="#appendix.configuration-metadata.format.repeated-items"></a>1.4. Repeated Metadata Items</h3>
1543-<div class="paragraph">
1544:<p>Objects with the same &#8220;property&#8221; and &#8220;group&#8221; name can appear multiple times within a metadata file.
1545-For example, you could bind two separate classes to the same prefix, with each having potentially overlapping property names.
1546-While the same names appearing in the metadata multiple times should not be common, consumers of metadata should take care to ensure that they support it.</p>
--
1633-<td class="content">
1634-We recommend that you use an <code>Enum</code> for those two values instead.
1635:If your IDE supports it, this is by far the most effective approach to auto-completion.
1636-</td>
1637-</tr>
--
1644-<p>Providers are a powerful way to attach semantics to a property.
1645-In this section, we define the official providers that you can use for your own hints.
1646:However, your favorite IDE may implement some of these or none of them.
1647-Also, it could eventually provide its own.</p>
1648-</div>
--
1654-</td>
1655-<td class="content">
1656:As this is a new feature, IDE vendors must catch up with how it works.
1657-Adoption times naturally vary.
1658-</td>
--
1712-<td class="content">
1713-Only one provider can be active for a given property, but you can specify several providers if they can all manage the property <em>in some way</em>.
1714:Make sure to place the most powerful provider first, as the IDE must use the first one in the JSON section that it can handle.
1715-If no provider for a given property is supported, no special content assistance is provided, either.
1716-</td>
--
1728-</div>
1729-<div class="paragraph">
1730:<p>The following example offers <code>on</code> and <code>off</code> as auto-completion values for <code>system.state</code>:</p>
1731-</div>
1732-<div class="listingblock">
--
1854-<li>
1855-<p>Any <code>java.lang.Enum</code>: Lists the possible values for the property.
1856:(We recommend defining the property with the <code>Enum</code> type, as no further hint should be required for the IDE to auto-complete the values)</p>
1857-</li>
1858-<li>
1859:<p><code>java.nio.charset.Charset</code>: Supports auto-completion of charset/encoding values (such as <code>UTF-8</code>)</p>
1860-</li>
1861-<li>
1862:<p><code>java.util.Locale</code>: auto-completion of locales (such as <code>en_US</code>)</p>
1863-</li>
1864-<li>
1865:<p><code>org.springframework.util.MimeType</code>: Supports auto-completion of content type values (such as <code>text/plain</code>)</p>
1866-</li>
1867-<li>
1868:<p><code>org.springframework.core.io.Resource</code>: Supports auto-completion of Spring’s Resource abstraction to refer to a file on the filesystem or on the classpath (such as <code>classpath:/sample.properties</code>)</p>
1869-</li>

